 {"id":"ft-eqtcq","title":"aegis_entropy_anomaly::EProcess::update propagates NaN e_value; permanently disables rejection","description":"EProcess::update calls likelihood_ratio(h, baseline_mean, baseline_std, collapse_mean, collapse_std). If any f64 input is NaN, log_h0 and log_h1 both become NaN, log_lr = NaN - NaN = NaN, log_lr.exp() = NaN, and clamp(1e-6, 1e6) passes NaN through because f64::clamp does not reject NaN. self.e_value *= NaN = NaN. The final clamp(1e-100, max_e) at update:226 also passes NaN through. Future is_rejected() returns (NaN >= threshold) = false, silently disabling anomaly detection for the lifetime of this EProcess. Matches ft-b4l62 / ft-yskcu / ft-c17iw / ft-n4fdx pattern — fail-closed on non-finite inputs at the update() boundary.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-22T18:03:02.334443Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-22T18:05:25.492018Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T18:05:25.491748Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"ft-eu0no","title":"[review][HIGH] PolicyEngine rate limiter fresh-per-MCP-request makes rate_limit config non-functional across all MCP tools","description":"Proactive policy.rs audit round 20. policy.rs:2077-2088 defines RateLimiter with state HashMaps pane_counts and global_counts owned BY the PolicyEngine struct. mcp_helpers.rs:97-107 build_policy_engine returns a fresh PolicyEngine every call (no Arc, no shared Mutex). grep confirms build_policy_engine is called at mcp_tools.rs:1130/1514/2029/2272/2332/3187/3319 and at the NEW ft-x86z2 helper at :187 — every MCP tool invocation constructs a fresh engine with empty HashMaps. Effect: config.safety.rate_limit_per_pane and rate_limit_global are non-functional for ALL MCP flows. Every request starts with current=0 less than limit=N so authorize never denies on rate grounds. ft-x86z2's new gate inherits the bug. Malicious MCP client can flood any mutation endpoint without backoff. Validation: build_policy_engine has no Arc/Mutex/thread_local sharing. RateLimiter HashMaps at policy.rs:2085-2087 are plain owned maps. 9 distinct build_policy_engine call sites in mcp_tools.rs each at per-request handler entry. Contrast: connector_outbound_bridge.rs:833 has set_policy_engine/policy_engine accessors holding a long-lived engine — long-lived is a known pattern, just not used for MCP. Fix: thread Arc-Mutex-PolicyEngine into each ToolHandler at construction, OR extract RateLimiter into Arc-Mutex-RateLimiter inside PolicyEngine. Acceptance: call wa.send N+1 times where N equals rate_limit_per_pane; assert N+1-th returns MCP_ERR_POLICY with rate-limit reason. Related ft-ym8nq LOW (deny-path not tested) would silently skip the rate-limit branch anyway. Severity HIGH: advertised defense that does not work. Audit round 20, 2026-04-23.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"jemanuel","created_at":"2026-04-23T20:27:18.613535Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T20:30:37.575912Z","sour